Find the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the matrix A = 
\begin{pmatrix}
 3 & 2 \\
 1 & 4 \\
\end{pmatrix}

Hint: The eigenvalues can be found by solving the characteristic equation det(A - λI) = 0, where I is the identity matrix and λ is the eigenvalue. The eigenvectors can be found by solving the equation (A - λI)x = 0, where x is the eigenvector corresponding to the eigenvalue λ.
